The paper discusses the development of a modelling language for planning technology, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning and scheduling (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of this language in domains such as space exploration (cs.RO) and manufacturing (cs.SY), which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the modelling power of the language, which could be of interest to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
